1
00:00:00,190 --> 00:00:04,310
Characters, actions, places, occupations,

2
00:00:04,334 --> 00:00:08,334
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

3
00:00:04,350 --> 00:00:09,220
and events in this series are fictional and
created for entertainment purposes only.

4
00:00:09,330 --> 00:00:13,970
They are not intended to urge
or promote any behavior in the series.

5
00:00:14,010 --> 00:00:16,400
Viewer discretion is advised.

6
00:00:16,720 --> 00:00:18,280
You mustered the courage
to break up with your boyfriend.

7
00:00:18,310 --> 00:00:19,800
Why don’t you try something new?

8
00:00:19,870 --> 00:00:21,500
Trust me. You can do it.

9
00:00:21,570 --> 00:00:24,380
There’s a chance
that we will get back together.

10
00:00:24,410 --> 00:00:25,550
We had a brief kiss.

11
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:26,900
You’re okay with it, right?

12
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:29,250
Didn’t you say I’m not your type?

13
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,400
You can be my type for one night.

14
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:32,030
Bambi.

15
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:33,500
You get the wrong person.

16
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,370
We shouldn’t have kissed that night.

17
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:37,000
Now, it’s hard to see you
as just a sister.

18
00:00:37,030 --> 00:00:37,740
I’m sorry.

19
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:39,500
I didn’t know that she would come back.

20
00:00:40,260 --> 00:00:42,090
Are you still interested
in being more than a one-night stand?

21
00:00:58,090 --> 00:01:02,600
Thank you, everyone,
for showing your support for Fiona and me.

22
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:06,160
All the promotional videos for the brand.

23
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:07,800
Don’t you think they look great?

24
00:01:08,140 --> 00:01:10,020
Yes.

25
00:01:12,860 --> 00:01:17,010
Please give a round of applause
to Prim Pariyakorn Rungruengsuk,

26
00:01:17,110 --> 00:01:19,390
the director of these videos
and my girlfriend.

27
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:26,500
What genres of music
are you into right now?

28
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:30,500
Didn’t you say
you knew everything about me?

29
00:02:31,410 --> 00:02:33,200
You can’t even remember
the music that I like.

30
00:02:34,290 --> 00:02:36,300
Time passes, people change.

31
00:02:36,460 --> 00:02:39,310
Do you still listen to the same music
as in high school?

32
00:02:40,270 --> 00:02:41,300
Yes.

33
00:02:41,890 --> 00:02:42,690
See?

34
00:02:43,110 --> 00:02:45,010
You are attached to the past.

35
00:02:45,530 --> 00:02:50,520
You keep going back to the same memories
and the same people.

36
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,980
You always find a way
to talk about yourself.

37
00:03:00,450 --> 00:03:02,300
Why don’t you try to listen
to disco music?

38
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:05,890
I don’t like dancing.

39
00:03:08,010 --> 00:03:09,190
What about metal music?

40
00:03:13,420 --> 00:03:14,490
It’s too heavy.

41
00:03:16,570 --> 00:03:17,700
What about sexy music?

42
00:03:29,690 --> 00:03:30,890
Can you stop joking around?

43
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:37,600
Or…

44
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:43,200
do you want to listen to…

45
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:45,600
my style?

46
00:03:51,130 --> 00:03:52,180
Knock it off.

47
00:03:52,210 --> 00:03:54,200
I didn’t let you tag along to joke around.

48
00:03:54,579 --> 00:03:55,800
I’m not joking around.

49
00:03:56,340 --> 00:03:58,100
I’m just thinking about
when we were in college.

50
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:01,770
When I waited for you
to buy vinyl records at a thrift store.

51
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:06,800
You told me
you wanted to make a lot of money.

52
00:04:06,830 --> 00:04:09,300
So you could buy as many vinyl records
as you wanted.

53
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,440
You finally achieved your goal.

54
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:14,580
Not really. I still need to be careful
when spending money.

55
00:04:14,610 --> 00:04:16,130
I have to take care of my mom and sister.

56
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:19,329
Unlike you, I can’t just point
and buy whatever, and I have to work.

57
00:04:19,750 --> 00:04:21,200
Who said I don’t work?

58
00:04:21,550 --> 00:04:22,400
I do.

59
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:23,990
I’m helping my mom manage her brand.

60
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:25,700
You know what?

61
00:04:26,370 --> 00:04:30,300
My goal is to be so successful

62
00:04:30,350 --> 00:04:35,980
that I’m on the list of
Asia’s most influential people under 30.

63
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,980
I hope you achieve it.

64
00:04:38,170 --> 00:04:39,980
You already have everything you need.

65
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,100
I can do it

66
00:04:42,980 --> 00:04:44,810
if I have you by my side as my girlfriend.

67
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:47,250
I am not your girlfriend yet.

68
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:49,450
I only give you a chance
to prove yourself.

69
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,630
Don’t get too excited.

70
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,760
You are unpredictable.

71
00:04:52,850 --> 00:04:54,550
I never know
which version of you will show up.

72
00:04:55,070 --> 00:04:56,800
There’s only one version of me.

73
00:04:57,810 --> 00:04:58,630
I’m pretty.

74
00:04:59,010 --> 00:04:59,980
I’m rich.

75
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:01,600
I’m cute.

76
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:03,850
I’m good at pampering you.

77
00:05:04,790 --> 00:05:06,210
I’m still that darling

78
00:05:06,460 --> 00:05:08,650
you have fallen in love with
since college.

79
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:12,700
I was in love with you.

80
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,560
At least, you once loved me.

81
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:26,200
Shasha.

82
00:05:26,970 --> 00:05:28,400
Do you have a new toothbrush?

83
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:30,700
Yes, it’s under the wash basin.

84
00:05:32,110 --> 00:05:33,600
Can you find it for me?

85
00:05:33,810 --> 00:05:35,980
I can’t find it. This is not my condo.

86
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:56,850
Don’t you have a regular toothbrush?

87
00:05:57,820 --> 00:05:58,600
No.

88
00:05:59,110 --> 00:06:00,900
An electric toothbrush
can clean teeth better.

89
00:06:00,970 --> 00:06:02,130
Don’t worry.

90
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:03,800
I get a new brush head for you.

91
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:05,610
I never share my toothbrush with anyone.

92
00:06:07,350 --> 00:06:08,200
Thank you.

93
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:12,080
You can keep it.

94
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,130
So you can use it next time you come here.

95
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:20,200
There won’t be next time.

96
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,600
You can throw it away after I use it.

97
00:06:22,830 --> 00:06:24,100
Are you sure?

98
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:26,200
How many times have you come here?

99
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:30,900
Is it the third time?

100
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:35,730
If my friend didn’t bail on me last night,
I wouldn’t come here.

101
00:06:36,990 --> 00:06:37,980
Fine.

102
00:06:38,409 --> 00:06:41,100
If it makes you feel better,
you can use whatever excuse you want

103
00:06:42,770 --> 00:06:45,100
to deny that you have a thing for me.

104
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,400
It’s fine by me.

105
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:02,100
It’s not easy to be a model.

106
00:07:02,610 --> 00:07:04,300
You can only eat healthy food.

107
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:05,800
You can’t have sweets.

108
00:07:07,020 --> 00:07:07,900
It’s okay.

109
00:07:08,330 --> 00:07:10,170
I can have something else
instead of sweets.

110
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,770
My appetite was fulfilled last night.

111
00:07:13,610 --> 00:07:15,500
Can you stop saying this stuff?

112
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:16,660
It’s so lame.

113
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:19,200
What do you want me to say?

114
00:07:19,330 --> 00:07:21,240
I still don’t know
how you want me to treat you.

115
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:23,240
You said you wanted us
to be friends with benefits.

116
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:25,900
But right now,
we are doing only half of it.

117
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,330
You’re doing it again.

118
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:31,500
We slept together. So we got the benefits.

119
00:07:31,650 --> 00:07:33,300
But we are not friends.

120
00:07:35,740 --> 00:07:36,600
Okay.

121
00:07:37,220 --> 00:07:39,290
My name is Gorya.

122
00:07:39,310 --> 00:07:40,570
I’m 24.

123
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,040
My family opens a diner.

124
00:07:42,060 --> 00:07:43,050
I’m an only child.

125
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:45,710
My parents wanted me to be a doctor.
But I chose to study fashion.

126
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:46,250
My favorite is red.

127
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:47,380
I like listening to rock music
and ghost stories,

128
00:07:47,409 --> 00:07:48,370
but I’m scared of ghosts.

129
00:07:48,409 --> 00:07:50,010
My longest relationship is one year long.

130
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,650
We broke up because she cheated on me.

131
00:07:51,970 --> 00:07:53,610
I wasn’t sad for long
because I’d rather focus on work.

132
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:54,640
I don’t care because I’m pretty.

133
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:58,500
My biggest goal is to start
my own clothing brand named Gorya.

134
00:07:59,120 --> 00:07:59,800
That’s all.

135
00:08:00,530 --> 00:08:01,500
Now you know me.

136
00:08:02,310 --> 00:08:03,200
Your turn.

137
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:05,050
My name is Shasha.

138
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,240
I’m 25.

139
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:07,510
I’m the only child.

140
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:10,230
My mom took me to auditions since I was 8.

141
00:08:10,260 --> 00:08:11,400
My nanny was my friend.

142
00:08:11,430 --> 00:08:12,950
My closest friend is my manager.

143
00:08:12,980 --> 00:08:14,000
My favorite color is black.

144
00:08:14,030 --> 00:08:15,090
I like classical music.

145
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,960
I’ve had only one girlfriend.

146
00:08:16,990 --> 00:08:18,900
Then I realized that
I don’t want to be in a relationship.

147
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:20,580
I don’t like taking responsibility
for other people’s feelings.

148
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,730
I just want to do whatever I want
and go wherever I want.

149
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:24,340
I don’t dream of tomorrow.

150
00:08:25,450 --> 00:08:26,700
I just enjoy today.

151
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,210
What?

152
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:45,980
Are you the kid
in the Crocodile toothbrush ad?

153
00:08:47,230 --> 00:08:49,600
You played a tooth worm.

154
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:52,790
Be careful, tooth worms are dangerous.

155
00:08:52,930 --> 00:08:53,900
Stop it.

156
00:08:54,380 --> 00:08:56,430
It’s been ages.
How can you still remember it?

157
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:01,100
I think we can be friends.

158
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:02,600
You are not a bad person.

159
00:09:04,290 --> 00:09:07,000
I told you I’m a nice person.

160
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,000
Don’t get ahead of yourself.

161
00:09:11,460 --> 00:09:13,990
Even as friends,
we need to get to know each other first.

162
00:09:20,970 --> 00:09:22,130
I’ll get tissue for you.

163
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,260
Do you want a blueberry?

164
00:09:40,370 --> 00:09:42,100
You can catch a taxi home.

165
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:44,100
I’m going to meet Min at the gallery.

166
00:09:44,310 --> 00:09:45,200
Can I come with you?

167
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,000
I’m free today.

168
00:09:47,340 --> 00:09:49,200
Didn’t you say you are working now?

169
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:50,670
You should focus on your work.

170
00:09:51,010 --> 00:09:53,000
I have my own priority.

171
00:09:53,370 --> 00:09:56,890
You know that
I always put love before work.

172
00:09:56,950 --> 00:09:58,300
-Go home.
-No.

173
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,350
Bambi.

174
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:02,050
When did you get back?

175
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:05,400
Why didn’t you visit Zee?

176
00:10:15,770 --> 00:10:18,700
I’m sorry. Do I know you?

177
00:10:19,030 --> 00:10:20,700
Bambi, don’t you remember me?

178
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,700
I’m Pae, Zee’s friend.

179
00:10:24,350 --> 00:10:25,500
Zee? Who?

180
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:27,400
I don’t know anyone by that name.

181
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:28,460
Zee is…

182
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,850
I think you got the wrong person.

183
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,600
I don’t know you.

184
00:10:33,260 --> 00:10:35,490
You may have seen me on social media.

185
00:10:35,810 --> 00:10:38,600
If you’re my fan,
this is my personal time.

186
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:41,400
Bambi.

187
00:10:43,430 --> 00:10:44,120
Bambi.

188
00:10:44,180 --> 00:10:45,000
Ouch.

189
00:10:45,030 --> 00:10:47,000
Bambi, are you okay?

190
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:48,700
Why are you running away?

191
00:10:49,470 --> 00:10:51,400
I’m scared of a stalker like her.

192
00:10:54,340 --> 00:10:55,130
Ouch.

193
00:10:56,390 --> 00:10:58,170
I think you should have
a doctor take a look.

194
00:10:58,190 --> 00:10:59,400
Maybe the injury is serious.

195
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:02,210
It’s okay. It’s not that serious.

196
00:11:02,450 --> 00:11:04,750
Why risk it?
The injury could get worse.

197
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:06,500
I’ll take you to the hospital.

198
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:10,700
Come on.

199
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,250
Her ankle is just sprained.

200
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,800
There is no broken bone.

201
00:11:15,470 --> 00:11:18,900
In the meantime, you should refrain
from walking too much and wearing heels.

202
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:19,980
What?

203
00:11:20,370 --> 00:11:23,650
I don’t like wearing flats.

204
00:11:23,980 --> 00:11:25,100
Bambi.

205
00:11:25,830 --> 00:11:27,980
Your ankle is injured. It’s not the time
to worry about your looks.

206
00:11:28,350 --> 00:11:29,400
It’s okay, Doctor.

207
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:31,100
I’ll take care of it.

208
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:31,970
Thank you.

209
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:42,500
Why did you run away?

210
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,450
Why didn’t you ask for my help?

211
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,900
I was afraid of a creep like her.

212
00:11:48,520 --> 00:11:50,200
She didn’t look like a creep.

213
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,770
It looked like she knew you.

214
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,400
She might be one of my mom’s fans.

215
00:11:56,670 --> 00:11:59,980
Or she might be a stalker
who wanted to get close to me.

216
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:03,700
This kind of thing could happen
to a pretty girl like me.

217
00:12:05,890 --> 00:12:07,400
Can you stop joking around?

218
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:11,600
Do you really not know her

219
00:12:12,550 --> 00:12:14,470
and the person named Zee
that she talked about?

220
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:18,450
No, I don’t know them.

221
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:19,900
Let’s forget about it.

222
00:12:21,630 --> 00:12:23,300
Will I be able to walk?

223
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,700
Wait here.

224
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:38,960
Come here.

225
00:12:42,020 --> 00:12:42,770
Easy.

226
00:12:46,370 --> 00:12:47,110
Easy.

227
00:12:59,180 --> 00:13:02,600
Will I ever find
an amazing girlfriend like you?

228
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,100
You will never find one.

229
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:10,500
I’m the type that if you lose me once,
you lose me forever.

230
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,200
I’m helping you

231
00:13:14,590 --> 00:13:15,630
because I feel bad for you.

232
00:13:23,630 --> 00:13:24,800
Hold them.

233
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,450
But I’m injured.

234
00:13:26,950 --> 00:13:27,900
Hold them.

235
00:13:28,910 --> 00:13:30,400
I’m a patient.

236
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:32,200
Hold them, Miss Bambi.

237
00:13:35,310 --> 00:13:36,950
You are so mean.

238
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:40,400
Here we go.

239
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:41,400
Be gentle.

240
00:13:41,450 --> 00:13:42,190
Ouch.

241
00:13:43,590 --> 00:13:44,900
I mean it.

242
00:13:45,980 --> 00:13:47,100
You’re at a hospital?

243
00:13:47,740 --> 00:13:49,100
Alright. It’s okay.

244
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,600
I hope her injury is not serious.

245
00:13:52,750 --> 00:13:53,500
Alright.

246
00:13:56,180 --> 00:13:57,600
How is Prim?

247
00:13:58,490 --> 00:13:59,980
I heard you said she’s at a hospital.

248
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:01,980
Prim is fine.

249
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:04,300
Bambi fell and sprained her ankle.

250
00:14:06,630 --> 00:14:08,800
So they end up getting back together.

251
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:11,970
They have a love-hate relationship.

252
00:14:13,070 --> 00:14:14,110
What about us?

253
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:21,870
You kissed me.

254
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:23,600
Aren’t you going to give me your answer?

255
00:14:24,210 --> 00:14:25,980
Don’t act all innocent.

256
00:14:26,910 --> 00:14:28,700
You set me up for it.

257
00:14:30,010 --> 00:14:32,200
But you also played along with it,
didn’t you?

258
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:37,900
I get it.

259
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:41,980
These feelings are new to you.

260
00:14:42,820 --> 00:14:44,500
I don’t mean to pressure you.

261
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:49,100
But I want you to know
that I really like you.

262
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:52,700
I know.

263
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,200
But don’t rush me.

264
00:14:55,580 --> 00:14:57,000
Give me some time.

265
00:14:57,930 --> 00:14:59,600
I want to be sure

266
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,500
that I’m not doing this
because I feel lonely

267
00:15:02,920 --> 00:15:04,170
or I have a moment of weakness.

268
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:09,200
I understand you.

269
00:15:09,630 --> 00:15:11,100
I don’t want to pressure you.

270
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:14,900
If I cross the line,
you can always tell me.

271
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:19,050
But I can’t really tell.
The line is very blurred to me.

272
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,800
If you want me to see you as a friend,

273
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:23,240
I don’t think I can do it.

274
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,450
You understand me, right?

275
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:29,000
Then…

276
00:15:29,820 --> 00:15:31,600
we should take things slowly.

277
00:15:32,330 --> 00:15:34,100
You need to give
a newbie like me some time.

278
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:36,890
I’ll see you as a senior in this.

279
00:15:56,240 --> 00:15:59,500
One day,
I’ll cross this line of senior-junior.

280
00:16:19,350 --> 00:16:21,700
Do you really need
to dig through this pile of clothes?

281
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:24,400
This is the life of
a hard-working stylist.

282
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:26,010
If you want to be my friend,

283
00:16:26,040 --> 00:16:27,410
then you need to get used to
this kind of life.

284
00:16:27,450 --> 00:16:29,500
These used clothes,

285
00:16:29,560 --> 00:16:32,500
if we know how to mix and match them,
we can sell them.

286
00:16:32,820 --> 00:16:34,600
Some of them are in terrible conditions.

287
00:16:35,210 --> 00:16:37,000
That’s why we need to hand-pick them.

288
00:16:38,210 --> 00:16:39,800
Since you’re here,
you should make yourself useful.

289
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:40,600
Sit down.

290
00:16:43,980 --> 00:16:47,650
Pick those that look pretty and cool.

291
00:16:47,970 --> 00:16:51,300
How will I know which ones you like?

292
00:16:51,890 --> 00:16:52,800
Just do it.

293
00:16:53,010 --> 00:16:53,980
I trust your taste.

294
00:17:02,290 --> 00:17:03,350
Do you want this one?

295
00:17:09,280 --> 00:17:09,980
Here.

296
00:17:10,450 --> 00:17:11,720
Do you want to take a break?

297
00:17:11,849 --> 00:17:13,800
It feels better to have you
take care of me.

298
00:17:14,010 --> 00:17:15,099
Hold it yourself.

299
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:24,599
I don’t think you can do it.

300
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:27,099
Don’t be so quick to judge.

301
00:17:27,140 --> 00:17:28,500
I’m still a newbie.

302
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:29,600
Give me some time.

303
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:32,600
This is the only time I took you here.

304
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:36,280
I’m afraid that your delicate skin
might get rashes, miss princess.

305
00:17:39,350 --> 00:17:42,500
These are what I picked and will buy.

306
00:17:42,550 --> 00:17:44,300
What? They are in the pile.

307
00:17:44,430 --> 00:17:45,640
I want them too.

308
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:47,950
If you picked them, then
you should have put them by your side.

309
00:17:47,980 --> 00:17:49,830
I only turned to talk to my friend
for a few seconds.

310
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:51,730
They are what I picked.

311
00:17:52,030 --> 00:17:52,870
I don’t care.

312
00:17:52,910 --> 00:17:54,200
I like them too.

313
00:17:54,690 --> 00:17:57,140
Miss, what are you going to do
with these clothes?

314
00:17:57,260 --> 00:17:58,260
I’m going to sell them.

315
00:17:58,620 --> 00:17:59,730
I’ll buy them.

316
00:18:00,140 --> 00:18:01,010
How much are they?

317
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,800
250 baht.

318
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:06,400
If you take all three,
the total will be 750.

319
00:18:06,850 --> 00:18:09,450
Okay. I’ll buy them.

320
00:18:10,350 --> 00:18:11,980
I’ll buy only the ones my friend wants.

321
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:15,600
Sure. You’ll take all three, right?

322
00:18:15,740 --> 00:18:18,120
I’m so lucky.
I don’t have to sell them somewhere else.

323
00:18:18,170 --> 00:18:19,980
I’ll go buy a drink and be right back.

324
00:18:20,010 --> 00:18:21,890
If you want them, you should hold them.

325
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:23,780
Anyone has the right to take them.

326
00:18:24,410 --> 00:18:25,240
Shasha.

327
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:29,400
Look. It’s only 20 baht per item.

328
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:32,400
You are spending money recklessly.

329
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:35,900
If it’s what you want, you will have it.

330
00:18:42,090 --> 00:18:43,200
How about this one?

331
00:18:43,660 --> 00:18:45,060
Do you really think it looks good?

332
00:18:45,540 --> 00:18:46,870
Yes. Don’t you like it?

333
00:18:47,340 --> 00:18:49,350
Do you think it looks good
if you have to wear it?

334
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:00,700
Put it here.

335
00:19:00,970 --> 00:19:02,800
I’ll ask my dad
to carry them upstairs later.

336
00:19:05,590 --> 00:19:07,600
I can help you carry them upstairs.

337
00:19:08,010 --> 00:19:08,800
No.

338
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,400
Only my close friends
are allowed to go upstairs.

339
00:19:11,710 --> 00:19:13,980
I’ve helped you all day,
but I’m still not your close friend?

340
00:19:13,990 --> 00:19:15,400
Not even close.

341
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:17,900
I feel discouraged.

342
00:19:19,540 --> 00:19:20,850
A girl like you…

343
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:24,600
it seems like you never struggle in life.

344
00:19:24,890 --> 00:19:25,850
Why?

345
00:19:26,590 --> 00:19:28,500
Do you think it’s easy to be a model?

346
00:19:29,010 --> 00:19:30,700
I’m not saying it’s easy.

347
00:19:31,140 --> 00:19:34,440
But it’s not as tough as my job.

348
00:19:36,340 --> 00:19:37,600
I want to be one too.

349
00:19:43,570 --> 00:19:44,320
Do I do it right?

350
00:19:50,580 --> 00:19:51,450
How am I doing?

351
00:19:51,790 --> 00:19:53,300
Do I have the potential to be a model?

352
00:19:59,540 --> 00:20:00,700
Do you know,

353
00:20:01,420 --> 00:20:03,350
before I got where I am,

354
00:20:03,910 --> 00:20:05,900
what kind of pain I had to endure?

355
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:31,050
Hey.

356
00:20:32,930 --> 00:20:35,100
I know this is a scene from Notting Hill.

357
00:20:37,380 --> 00:20:38,900
It’s my favorite movie.

358
00:20:39,230 --> 00:20:40,900
We have the same favorite movie.

359
00:20:41,780 --> 00:20:43,340
I want to tell you this.

360
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:45,100
My life is not easy.

361
00:20:45,450 --> 00:20:47,500
My mom was very controlling
about how I looked.

362
00:20:47,730 --> 00:20:49,300
She always corrected my posture.

363
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:51,180
I’ve never had a friend.

364
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:52,800
All I did was go to auditions.

365
00:20:53,930 --> 00:20:55,900
Try to live like that for ten years.

366
00:20:56,060 --> 00:20:57,100
Then you will understand me.

367
00:20:58,470 --> 00:21:00,200
Fine. I’m sorry.

368
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:01,980
It’s okay.

369
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:03,200
I get it.

370
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:06,280
Those who don’t know me
will think my life is perfect.

371
00:21:10,270 --> 00:21:11,250
I’m leaving.

372
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:16,180
Today, I’m your friend,
but I haven’t gotten any benefits.

373
00:21:17,730 --> 00:21:18,800
Shasha.

374
00:21:19,840 --> 00:21:21,900
Stop it. I’m not in the mood.
You should leave.

375
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,500
Okay. Bye.

376
00:21:38,830 --> 00:21:40,500
She still doesn’t answer your calls?

377
00:21:40,580 --> 00:21:41,600
It’s been three days.

378
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:43,400
No.

379
00:21:43,630 --> 00:21:46,200
I still don’t understand
why she had to run away.

380
00:21:46,980 --> 00:21:51,210
Did she ever tell you what happened
while she was abroad?

381
00:21:51,780 --> 00:21:53,300
No.

382
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,850
She only told me she went to study abroad.

383
00:21:56,220 --> 00:21:58,160
She was not in the mood
and wanted to get back at her mom.

384
00:21:58,190 --> 00:21:59,980
So she contacted no one in Thailand.

385
00:22:00,010 --> 00:22:00,800
That’s all.

386
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:04,800
If you’re curious, you need to dig up.

387
00:22:06,030 --> 00:22:07,700
Social media is for snooping on people.

388
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:38,530
I REALLY MISS YOU.

389
00:22:52,670 --> 00:22:53,900
Does your ankle still hurt?

390
00:22:54,610 --> 00:22:56,250
Did you go to the doctor’s appointment?

391
00:22:57,080 --> 00:22:58,250
It doesn’t hurt anymore.

392
00:22:58,780 --> 00:23:00,760
I’m just wearing the bandage
to get your sympathy.

393
00:23:03,110 --> 00:23:05,880
Why did you turn off your phone
and not reply to my texts?

394
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:10,650
I wanted to have an introverted moment.

395
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:13,450
I went off the grid to make you miss me.

396
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:21,200
I have something to give you.

397
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:24,960
Ouch.

398
00:23:25,530 --> 00:23:27,100
Stop, Bambi.

399
00:23:30,990 --> 00:23:32,600
What do you want? I’ll get it for you.

400
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:37,090
The vinyl records over there.

401
00:23:37,450 --> 00:23:38,600
Take all of them.

402
00:23:44,770 --> 00:23:46,220
Wow, Bambi.

403
00:23:49,380 --> 00:23:51,300
They are all rare records.

404
00:23:53,130 --> 00:23:53,980
Yes.

405
00:23:54,220 --> 00:23:55,400
They are…

406
00:23:55,970 --> 00:23:57,000
yours.

407
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:59,640
I can’t take them.

408
00:23:59,690 --> 00:24:01,800
Your dad really treasured them.

409
00:24:02,450 --> 00:24:04,930
He is dead. He wouldn’t mind.

410
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:06,290
You can take them.

411
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:09,060
I can’t take them.

412
00:24:09,110 --> 00:24:10,500
It’s worth thousands of baht.

413
00:24:12,220 --> 00:24:13,180
You should take them.

414
00:24:13,220 --> 00:24:15,150
My mom and I won’t play them anyway.

415
00:24:21,290 --> 00:24:23,400
I’m sure
you will take better care of them.

416
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:30,800
Thank you.

417
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:33,980
I don’t have to buy records for a while.

418
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:35,980
Don’t forget to listen to them every day.

419
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:39,100
This one is so cool, Bambi.

420
00:24:58,560 --> 00:24:59,400
Bambi.

421
00:24:59,860 --> 00:25:00,600
Yes.

422
00:25:01,250 --> 00:25:03,500
If you have a problem,
you can always tell me.

423
00:25:05,810 --> 00:25:07,630
No matter what our relationship is,

424
00:25:09,140 --> 00:25:10,870
I’ll always care about you.

425
00:25:13,140 --> 00:25:14,900
Why are you saying
these sweet words to me?

426
00:25:21,710 --> 00:25:23,600
I like staying like this.

427
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:43,000
Thank you.

428
00:25:43,460 --> 00:25:44,700
Can you look at the camera?

429
00:25:45,580 --> 00:25:46,970
Please smile at the camera.

430
00:25:47,450 --> 00:25:49,300
One, two, three. Beautiful.

431
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:51,510
One, two, three, Great.

432
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:56,010
Congratulations, Bambi.

433
00:25:56,180 --> 00:25:57,270
Thank you.

434
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:06,200
Did you find out what happened
when she was abroad?

435
00:26:06,710 --> 00:26:07,840
I haven’t talked to her.

436
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:09,500
I’m waiting until she’s ready to talk.

437
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:11,800
If she wants to tell me, she will.

438
00:26:14,910 --> 00:26:16,550
She looks really pretty today.

439
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:17,690
You think so?

440
00:26:18,090 --> 00:26:19,210
She always looks pretty like this.

441
00:26:25,470 --> 00:26:26,720
Min. Prim.

442
00:26:26,740 --> 00:26:27,600
Praew.

443
00:26:27,860 --> 00:26:29,700
You work for this event? I didn’t know it.

444
00:26:29,980 --> 00:26:31,500
I’m shooting behind-the-scenes pictures.

445
00:26:31,600 --> 00:26:33,300
Min helped me get this job.

446
00:26:36,080 --> 00:26:37,330
Why didn’t you tell me?

447
00:26:38,470 --> 00:26:40,300
I just helped her get a job.

448
00:26:40,560 --> 00:26:41,980
I don’t need to tell you about it.

449
00:26:43,250 --> 00:26:45,300
Excuse me.
I’ll go and give her the flower.

450
00:26:45,960 --> 00:26:47,200
Fine.

451
00:26:47,670 --> 00:26:49,000
You bought it for her.

452
00:26:49,140 --> 00:26:52,300
It’s the flower from our company.
I already asked for an invoice for it.

453
00:27:00,190 --> 00:27:00,900
Min.

454
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:04,500
Thank you for this job.

455
00:27:05,140 --> 00:27:06,500
It saves my life.

456
00:27:07,470 --> 00:27:08,370
It’s not a big deal.

457
00:27:08,390 --> 00:27:10,150
When you become famous,
your fee will be high.

458
00:27:10,180 --> 00:27:11,100
So I’d better hire you now.

459
00:27:11,650 --> 00:27:14,500
If it is your job, I won’t take any pay.

460
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:16,500
I want…

461
00:27:19,040 --> 00:27:20,600
What? What do you want?

462
00:27:20,780 --> 00:27:22,500
Didn’t you tell me
you wouldn’t cross the line?

463
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:23,900
You are so pretty today.

464
00:27:24,510 --> 00:27:25,800
I can’t help it.

465
00:27:26,490 --> 00:27:27,900
You need to be patient.

466
00:27:28,390 --> 00:27:30,200
If you want good stuff,
it will take some time.

467
00:27:48,420 --> 00:27:49,980
It’s done, Shasha.

468
00:27:50,540 --> 00:27:52,060
You can change your outfit over there.

469
00:27:52,090 --> 00:27:53,100
Thank you.

470
00:28:00,840 --> 00:28:01,600
Sha.

471
00:28:03,500 --> 00:28:04,300
Claire.

472
00:28:06,250 --> 00:28:07,600
It’s been a while since we last met.

473
00:28:08,540 --> 00:28:09,700
I’m busy.

474
00:28:12,730 --> 00:28:13,700
I miss you.

475
00:28:16,900 --> 00:28:17,600
Yeah.

476
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:22,200
I think that night…

477
00:28:22,950 --> 00:28:24,200
it was really fun.

478
00:28:25,580 --> 00:28:26,610
Why didn’t you contact me?

479
00:28:26,850 --> 00:28:28,080
Did I do something wrong?

480
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:31,500
No, you didn’t.

481
00:28:32,100 --> 00:28:33,200
It just…

482
00:28:36,430 --> 00:28:37,700
We were just having fun, right?

483
00:28:38,050 --> 00:28:39,230
I know.

484
00:28:39,850 --> 00:28:40,850
But…

485
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:42,800
I want to go to your condo again.

486
00:28:43,580 --> 00:28:44,900
I promise that this time,

487
00:28:45,300 --> 00:28:46,730
it will be unforgettable.

488
00:29:02,570 --> 00:29:03,250
Mod.

489
00:29:03,870 --> 00:29:05,620
Why is the model not putting the dress on?

490
00:29:05,650 --> 00:29:07,050
The show is about to begin.

491
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:09,210
Gorya, the model…

492
00:29:09,360 --> 00:29:10,250
She what?

493
00:29:24,620 --> 00:29:25,500
Do your job, Mod.

494
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:27,400
We are here to work.

495
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:29,200
We don’t have time to fool around.

496
00:29:40,070 --> 00:29:41,050
Wow.

497
00:29:42,430 --> 00:29:44,300
You remember my favorite flower.

498
00:29:45,310 --> 00:29:46,500
Can you give it to me later?

499
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:48,450
The flower is from Lady Bird.

500
00:29:49,020 --> 00:29:50,500
Stop making excuses.

501
00:29:53,180 --> 00:29:54,400
Pony.

502
00:29:54,990 --> 00:29:56,700
-Hello.
-Hi, sis.

503
00:29:56,830 --> 00:29:59,270
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

504
00:29:59,640 --> 00:30:00,900
Pony.

505
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:02,230
Prim, this is Pony.

506
00:30:02,260 --> 00:30:03,850
She owns a women’s clothes business.

507
00:30:04,500 --> 00:30:06,750
She’s launching a new collection.

508
00:30:06,780 --> 00:30:08,700
She’s looking for a production team
for her promotional video.

509
00:30:09,280 --> 00:30:11,000
Hello, Pony. I’m Prim.

510
00:30:11,130 --> 00:30:12,450
Hello.

511
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:17,550
Bambi told me
that you produced the Fiona ad.

512
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:19,710
She said you are talented.

513
00:30:19,740 --> 00:30:22,500
I’m looking for a production team
that understands what I want.

514
00:30:22,700 --> 00:30:24,330
So we can work together for a long time.

515
00:30:24,540 --> 00:30:25,900
Can I have your contact info?

516
00:30:25,930 --> 00:30:27,360
I’ll have my employee contact you.

517
00:30:27,390 --> 00:30:28,300
Sure.

518
00:30:32,230 --> 00:30:32,720
Here.

519
00:30:32,750 --> 00:30:34,200
Thank you.

520
00:30:34,340 --> 00:30:35,090
See you.

521
00:30:35,130 --> 00:30:36,180
See you. Thank you.

522
00:30:38,980 --> 00:30:40,200
Let’s take pictures.

523
00:30:44,780 --> 00:30:46,200
Stop it, Bambi.

524
00:30:46,420 --> 00:30:47,900
You don’t need to get this close.

525
00:30:48,930 --> 00:30:50,400
We need to create buzz.

526
00:30:52,150 --> 00:30:53,200
What buzz?

527
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:58,400
You’ll see.

528
00:32:16,370 --> 00:32:20,900
Thank you, everyone,
for showing your support for Fiona and me.

529
00:32:21,410 --> 00:32:25,900
My mom made Yanin a legendary brand
a long time ago.

530
00:32:26,340 --> 00:32:27,970
The legend is still alive.

531
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:29,970
But now we are starting a new chapter.

532
00:32:31,510 --> 00:32:34,240
Things that are so old and outdated

533
00:32:35,100 --> 00:32:37,000
that we thought
they would never have a comeback.

534
00:32:37,800 --> 00:32:39,600
If we work hard,

535
00:32:39,810 --> 00:32:43,500
I believe
it can regain its top spot one day.

536
00:32:49,340 --> 00:32:50,200
Hold on.

537
00:32:51,080 --> 00:32:53,200
There’s another important person.

538
00:32:53,630 --> 00:32:56,200
All the promotional videos for the brand.

539
00:32:56,420 --> 00:32:57,700
Don’t you think they look great?

540
00:32:57,980 --> 00:33:00,150
Yes.

541
00:33:02,780 --> 00:33:06,800
Please give a round of applause
to Prim Pariyakorn Rungruengsuk,

542
00:33:07,060 --> 00:33:09,800
the director of these videos
and my girlfriend.

543
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:19,040
Why didn’t you tell me?

544
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:37,350
Can you step closer?

545
00:33:37,430 --> 00:33:39,460
-Please smile.
-Can you look at the camera?

546
00:33:40,660 --> 00:33:41,480
Nice.

547
00:33:41,500 --> 00:33:43,250
Can I have one more picture?

548
00:33:50,720 --> 00:33:51,800
You are leaving?

549
00:33:54,890 --> 00:33:56,600
Aren’t you going to the afterparty?

550
00:33:57,680 --> 00:33:58,400
No.

551
00:33:58,580 --> 00:34:00,300
I’ve gone through random bullshit today.

552
00:34:02,130 --> 00:34:04,900
Are you upset about Prim and Bambi?

553
00:34:05,600 --> 00:34:07,000
Don’t tell me…

554
00:34:07,210 --> 00:34:08,250
you are still not over her?

555
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:09,800
It’s none of your business.

556
00:34:10,260 --> 00:34:12,300
I’m not the type
who can get over quickly like you.

557
00:34:13,199 --> 00:34:14,100
What do you mean?

558
00:34:17,310 --> 00:34:19,100
Are you jealous to see me with Claire?

559
00:34:21,750 --> 00:34:22,889
Why would I be jealous?

560
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:25,810
I slept with her once.

561
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:27,600
She likes me,
but I don’t feel the same way.

562
00:34:27,900 --> 00:34:28,739
I don’t want to know.

563
00:34:36,330 --> 00:34:37,100
Let me go.

564
00:34:37,380 --> 00:34:38,500
I want to go home.

565
00:34:39,110 --> 00:34:40,409
Do you want to go to my condo?

566
00:34:40,710 --> 00:34:41,400
Let me go.

567
00:34:45,630 --> 00:34:46,500
Gorya.

568
00:34:48,900 --> 00:34:49,670
Are you okay?

569
00:34:51,480 --> 00:34:54,300
It’s nothing. I’m leaving.

570
00:34:57,090 --> 00:34:58,300
Congratulations, Prim.

571
00:34:58,630 --> 00:35:00,800
You and Bambi officially became a couple.

572
00:35:01,570 --> 00:35:05,900
Those who have a crush on you
will go home and cry.

573
00:35:07,320 --> 00:35:08,600
You don’t need to congratulate me.

574
00:35:08,860 --> 00:35:10,440
Bambi just wanted to create buzz.

575
00:35:13,940 --> 00:35:14,750
Gorya.

576
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:17,520
Aren’t you going to the afterparty?

577
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:19,400
No.

578
00:35:19,760 --> 00:35:21,300
I have nothing to celebrate today.

579
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:25,500
Congratulations.

580
00:35:34,500 --> 00:35:36,600
Are you going to keep them both?

581
00:35:36,820 --> 00:35:38,200
Won’t you give me a chance?

582
00:35:38,940 --> 00:35:39,980
What are you talking about?

583
00:35:51,900 --> 00:35:54,200
Bambi, can you take a picture with me?

584
00:35:56,580 --> 00:35:57,700
Ready?

585
00:36:01,350 --> 00:36:02,300
Thank you.

586
00:36:10,390 --> 00:36:11,600
Why did you do that?

587
00:36:11,880 --> 00:36:13,600
I haven’t agreed to it.

588
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:16,880
Calm down.

589
00:36:16,910 --> 00:36:18,100
I’ve thought it through.

590
00:36:18,490 --> 00:36:19,600
This will benefit you.

591
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:20,800
How?

592
00:36:21,410 --> 00:36:23,280
People are paying attention
to this nonsense.

593
00:36:29,230 --> 00:36:30,800
The buzz will put you in the spotlight.

594
00:36:31,940 --> 00:36:32,490
You win.

595
00:36:32,710 --> 00:36:33,580
I win.

596
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:35,600
People pay attention to my brand.

597
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:38,300
You have new connections from this event.

598
00:36:38,780 --> 00:36:41,210
I don’t want to get new jobs this way.

599
00:36:41,750 --> 00:36:45,200
I work hard to get where I am
without help from you or your mom.

600
00:36:50,320 --> 00:36:51,980
But that’s not enough, Prim.

601
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:55,500
These connections can help you
achieve your dream.

602
00:36:55,900 --> 00:36:57,940
An international award, don’t you want it?

603
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:59,900
Yes, but not like this.

604
00:37:00,340 --> 00:37:02,700
I can do it myself.
I don’t need help from anyone.

605
00:37:09,620 --> 00:37:10,700
Anyone?

606
00:37:16,940 --> 00:37:18,600
I’m just anyone to you?

607
00:37:21,410 --> 00:37:23,500
I did all this for you.

608
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:26,500
You’ve never done anything for me, Bambi.

609
00:37:26,740 --> 00:37:28,300
You did everything for your own benefit.

610
00:37:28,990 --> 00:37:29,980
Like always.

611
00:38:29,470 --> 00:38:30,400
Sure.

612
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:32,100
I’ll go get it.

613
00:38:32,500 --> 00:38:33,900
Under the counter, right?

614
00:38:34,290 --> 00:38:35,430
Sure. Bye.

615
00:38:37,180 --> 00:38:39,200
Praew. Where are you going?

616
00:38:39,860 --> 00:38:40,700
Min.

617
00:38:42,020 --> 00:38:44,200
I need to go to Blossom
to get something for Ant.

618
00:38:44,300 --> 00:38:45,600
Isn’t the bar closed today?

619
00:38:46,260 --> 00:38:47,390
She gave me the keys.

620
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:49,100
Do you need a ride?

621
00:38:49,670 --> 00:38:50,900
I’m going that way.

622
00:38:51,340 --> 00:38:52,590
Are you going that way?

623
00:38:52,620 --> 00:38:54,610
Or do you want me to ride with you?

624
00:38:55,380 --> 00:38:57,000
Stop flirting with me. Get in.

625
00:39:03,750 --> 00:39:05,900
I can’t give you an inch.

626
00:39:15,200 --> 00:39:18,200
I never saw the bar when it was empty.

627
00:39:20,260 --> 00:39:21,900
The bar closes once a week.

628
00:39:22,240 --> 00:39:23,900
You need to let her have a day off.

629
00:39:25,570 --> 00:39:26,600
Where is it?

630
00:39:29,680 --> 00:39:30,600
I found it.

631
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:33,300
I’ll let her know.

632
00:39:43,820 --> 00:39:44,900
Do you want a drink?

633
00:39:46,450 --> 00:39:47,700
I can make it for you.

634
00:39:48,310 --> 00:39:49,100
No.

635
00:39:49,250 --> 00:39:51,120
We can’t take her drink behind her back.

636
00:39:51,150 --> 00:39:52,700
She trusts you.

637
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:55,220
She won’t mind.

638
00:39:55,640 --> 00:39:56,600
We can have it.

639
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,850
She was the one
who taught me how to make drinks.

640
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:00,500
Let’s have a drink.

641
00:40:02,410 --> 00:40:04,700
There are only us in this bar tonight.

642
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:08,400
Is it a good idea?

643
00:40:09,520 --> 00:40:10,700
If it’s not good,

644
00:40:11,370 --> 00:40:13,000
I won’t ask you to do it.

645
00:41:08,070 --> 00:41:08,750
Hey.

646
00:41:09,070 --> 00:41:10,100
Do you know what?

647
00:41:10,590 --> 00:41:13,900
I wanted to be a bartender.

648
00:41:14,800 --> 00:41:18,400
But when I thought about it,
I didn’t think I could do it.

649
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:20,500
I’m a lightweight.

650
00:41:21,660 --> 00:41:22,650
I can tell.

651
00:41:23,660 --> 00:41:25,800
Your cheeks are all red.

652
00:41:27,290 --> 00:41:28,700
Is it that obvious?

653
00:41:30,590 --> 00:41:31,600
Can I ask you for real?

654
00:41:33,150 --> 00:41:34,600
Why do you like me?

655
00:41:36,430 --> 00:41:37,980
Can I tell you the truth?

656
00:41:40,430 --> 00:41:41,330
You are pretty.

657
00:41:41,700 --> 00:41:43,150
There are many pretty girls out there.

658
00:41:43,180 --> 00:41:44,500
Why don’t you like them?

659
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:47,850
Why are you pushing me away?

660
00:41:48,160 --> 00:41:49,500
I like you.

661
00:41:49,570 --> 00:41:51,900
Why are you telling me
to like someone else?

662
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:53,800
I’m not pushing you away.

663
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:58,700
I just want to know if I’m worth enough
for someone to fall for me.

664
00:42:00,420 --> 00:42:03,900
That jerk not only hurt your feelings,

665
00:42:04,160 --> 00:42:06,100
but he also ruined your self-confidence.

666
00:42:09,640 --> 00:42:10,500
Min.

667
00:42:12,170 --> 00:42:13,980
I want you to know…

668
00:42:15,730 --> 00:42:17,530
you are so cool.

669
00:42:18,030 --> 00:42:19,160
Do you know that?

670
00:42:19,540 --> 00:42:21,800
You are super cool.

671
00:42:22,510 --> 00:42:29,660
Even though I started to like you because
you are pretty, talented, and kind,

672
00:42:30,470 --> 00:42:34,200
I’ll always find new reasons
to fall for you.

673
00:42:35,560 --> 00:42:37,140
Even in the end,

674
00:42:37,980 --> 00:42:39,970
we may not end up together.

675
00:42:43,350 --> 00:42:46,500
You will be the last straight girl
that I fall for.

676
00:42:55,100 --> 00:42:57,000
What if I’m not straight anymore?

677
00:44:29,160 --> 00:44:31,210
I’m here to pick up the records
I ordered the other day.

678
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,600
How is your girlfriend?
I saw her fall the other day.

679
00:44:42,650 --> 00:44:43,600
She is now okay.

680
00:44:45,640 --> 00:44:46,500
Is it all done?

681
00:44:47,020 --> 00:44:47,810
Thank you.

682
00:45:00,190 --> 00:45:01,100
Excuse me.

683
00:45:02,820 --> 00:45:03,700
Yes.

684
00:45:04,670 --> 00:45:05,900
Can I ask you something?

685
00:45:08,010 --> 00:45:09,980
You came to talk to Bambi the other day.

686
00:45:10,300 --> 00:45:11,200
Do you remember?

687
00:45:12,340 --> 00:45:13,400
Yes.

688
00:45:13,830 --> 00:45:15,300
You were with her.

689
00:45:15,470 --> 00:45:16,300
Yes.

690
00:45:18,130 --> 00:45:19,980
Do you know Bambi?

691
00:45:20,540 --> 00:45:21,700
Yes.

692
00:45:22,030 --> 00:45:23,980
Her ex is my friend.

693
00:45:24,340 --> 00:45:28,700
I didn’t get why she pretended
that she didn’t know me.

694
00:45:29,310 --> 00:45:30,500
But now I get it.

695
00:45:31,110 --> 00:45:33,300
I guess she can’t deal with what happened.

696
00:45:34,730 --> 00:45:35,850
What happened?

697
00:45:37,530 --> 00:45:38,600
I’m sorry.

698
00:45:39,130 --> 00:45:41,300
What is your relationship with Bambi?

699
00:45:44,760 --> 00:45:45,700
I’m her girlfriend.

700
00:45:50,690 --> 00:45:53,910
Zee broke up with her girlfriend
to date Bambi.

701
00:45:53,990 --> 00:45:55,600
They were dating for around six months.

702
00:45:55,800 --> 00:45:57,600
They keep their relationship private.

703
00:45:57,780 --> 00:45:59,100
They didn’t go public.

704
00:45:59,740 --> 00:46:02,500
Zee told me that it was Bambi’s rule.

705
00:46:02,730 --> 00:46:07,160
She wanted to be sure about
their relationship before telling anyone.

706
00:46:07,620 --> 00:46:11,700
So Zee agreed
to keep their relationship a secret.

707
00:46:15,680 --> 00:46:17,300
Why did they break up?

708
00:46:19,800 --> 00:46:21,000
Zee told me

709
00:46:21,460 --> 00:46:23,550
that Bambi still couldn’t get over her ex.

710
00:46:24,290 --> 00:46:25,980
They had a big fight.

711
00:46:26,490 --> 00:46:27,600
It led to an accident.

712
00:46:29,850 --> 00:46:30,900
What accident?

713
00:46:36,410 --> 00:46:37,400
Gorya.

714
00:46:38,490 --> 00:46:39,400
Gorya.

715
00:46:42,260 --> 00:46:43,400
Wake up, sweetie.

716
00:46:44,180 --> 00:46:46,650
Why are you still sleeping when you have
an appointment with your friend?

717
00:46:46,680 --> 00:46:47,600
Wake up.

718
00:46:47,880 --> 00:46:48,750
Get up.

719
00:46:49,700 --> 00:46:51,010
An appointment with whom?

720
00:46:52,440 --> 00:46:53,390
I don’t have an appointment.

721
00:46:53,410 --> 00:46:55,980
Today is my day off.
I’m going to sleep until noon.

722
00:46:56,480 --> 00:46:57,980
Do you remember it wrong?

723
00:46:58,040 --> 00:46:59,610
She’s been waiting for you for a while.

724
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:00,400
Come on.

725
00:47:01,170 --> 00:47:01,900
Get up.

726
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:08,160
Who is she?

727
00:47:09,630 --> 00:47:11,800
It’s on the tip of my tongue.

728
00:47:13,510 --> 00:47:14,600
Shashasha.

729
00:47:15,100 --> 00:47:16,700
That’s her name.

730
00:47:19,750 --> 00:47:20,890
Shashasha?

731
00:47:20,930 --> 00:47:21,800
Yes.

732
00:47:23,130 --> 00:47:25,140
Don’t keep her waiting. Get up.

733
00:47:25,170 --> 00:47:25,870
Mom.

734
00:47:26,810 --> 00:47:28,200
Her name is Shasha.

735
00:47:28,630 --> 00:47:30,430
It’s the same.

736
00:47:30,460 --> 00:47:31,590
Come on. Get up.

737
00:47:32,560 --> 00:47:33,600
Get up now.

738
00:47:34,810 --> 00:47:36,600
It’s not good to keep her waiting.

739
00:47:38,210 --> 00:47:39,400
Enjoy your food.

740
00:47:39,760 --> 00:47:40,700
Thank you.

741
00:47:52,140 --> 00:47:53,200
What are you doing here?

742
00:47:53,460 --> 00:47:54,650
I want to get more sleep.

743
00:47:56,860 --> 00:47:59,900
Minced pork and basil stir-fry with water,
with low salt and spicy level,

744
00:48:00,240 --> 00:48:02,400
and served with a soft-boiled egg.

745
00:48:06,210 --> 00:48:07,200
What do you want?

746
00:48:09,240 --> 00:48:11,600
This is another thing
you need to learn about me.

747
00:48:12,070 --> 00:48:13,400
What games are you playing?

748
00:48:13,640 --> 00:48:16,200
There’s no need for us
to get to know each other anymore.

749
00:48:16,560 --> 00:48:17,800
Let’s call it quits.

750
00:48:18,630 --> 00:48:20,300
I won’t go to your condo again.

751
00:48:21,610 --> 00:48:22,500
It’s okay.

752
00:48:22,660 --> 00:48:24,700
I don’t want that from you anyway.

753
00:48:24,860 --> 00:48:26,450
I just want to be your friend.

754
00:48:28,860 --> 00:48:30,900
Is it that hard for you to find a friend?

755
00:48:32,210 --> 00:48:34,900
You’re not afraid to point out
when I do something wrong or lame.

756
00:48:35,190 --> 00:48:37,400
I want to have someone honest in my life.

757
00:48:38,970 --> 00:48:39,800
Fine.

758
00:48:40,250 --> 00:48:41,700
Miss high-maintenance…

759
00:48:43,120 --> 00:48:44,100
…model.

760
00:48:46,390 --> 00:48:47,530
Where are you taking me today?

761
00:49:10,250 --> 00:49:11,300
Hello, Bambi.

762
00:49:12,290 --> 00:49:13,600
Are you not mad at me anymore?

763
00:49:14,670 --> 00:49:17,170
Are you free?
Can you come out to meet me?

764
00:49:19,490 --> 00:49:20,800
No, I don’t want to go.

765
00:49:21,420 --> 00:49:23,100
I have something important to tell you.

766
00:49:23,680 --> 00:49:24,800
Please come to see me.

767
00:49:25,090 --> 00:49:26,330
I’ll send my location to you.

768
00:49:26,880 --> 00:49:27,980
I said I won’t go.

769
00:49:28,020 --> 00:49:28,600
Prim.

770
00:49:29,070 --> 00:49:29,730
Prim.

771
00:50:06,150 --> 00:50:07,300
What time is it, Min?

772
00:50:16,590 --> 00:50:17,700
11 o’clock.

773
00:50:20,810 --> 00:50:22,880
I was sleeping so comfortably
that I lost track of time.

774
00:50:27,760 --> 00:50:29,110
How do you feel?

775
00:50:31,160 --> 00:50:34,800
I’ve never woken up this late.

776
00:50:41,140 --> 00:50:43,000
I guess we had a great time last night.

777
00:50:43,610 --> 00:50:46,500
We cuddled and lost track of time.

778
00:50:51,810 --> 00:50:52,800
In the end,

779
00:50:53,370 --> 00:50:55,330
the person who told me
not to cross the line

780
00:50:55,360 --> 00:50:56,610
broke the rule herself.

781
00:50:59,710 --> 00:51:01,300
It’s just a physical thing.

782
00:51:02,230 --> 00:51:04,100
Emotionally, I’m still the same.

783
00:51:04,440 --> 00:51:05,700
We are still friends.

784
00:51:06,740 --> 00:51:09,900
What we did last night,
friends don’t do that.

785
00:51:11,930 --> 00:51:13,960
The friend zone ended

786
00:51:14,580 --> 00:51:16,830
when your lips touched mine.

787
00:51:30,300 --> 00:51:31,980
Min, stop hesitating.

788
00:51:32,640 --> 00:51:34,300
Cross the line and be on my side.

789
00:51:37,660 --> 00:51:39,100
Don’t rush me.

790
00:51:39,670 --> 00:51:41,700
I’m still learning it.

791
00:51:42,390 --> 00:51:43,980
What we did last night,

792
00:51:45,360 --> 00:51:47,250
it doesn’t seem like
you need to learn anymore.

793
00:51:47,950 --> 00:51:50,650
You are so good at it,
like you’re an expert.

794
00:51:58,480 --> 00:51:59,980
I don’t want to wake up.

795
00:52:30,800 --> 00:52:32,400
Being friends,

796
00:52:32,780 --> 00:52:35,050
we don’t need to be this close.

797
00:52:36,630 --> 00:52:38,500
We aren’t following the rules of friends.

798
00:52:38,970 --> 00:52:40,700
We are following the rules of shooting.

799
00:52:41,060 --> 00:52:42,500
We need to hit the target.

800
00:52:44,280 --> 00:52:45,870
So I have to get close to teach you.

801
00:52:49,940 --> 00:52:51,100
Be careful.

802
00:52:51,830 --> 00:52:53,050
If you aren’t careful,

803
00:52:53,830 --> 00:52:55,130
you might become the target yourself.

804
00:52:57,050 --> 00:52:59,400
I won’t be an easy target.

805
00:53:02,160 --> 00:53:03,200
I’ll wait and see.

806
00:53:03,980 --> 00:53:05,550
When I set my sights on something,

807
00:53:06,130 --> 00:53:07,600
I’ve never missed.

808
00:53:56,760 --> 00:53:57,500
Prim.

809
00:54:30,170 --> 00:54:32,110
Stop filming me.
I don’t look good right now.

810
00:54:32,710 --> 00:54:33,600
It’s not true.

811
00:54:34,290 --> 00:54:36,530
You’ve never left your house
if you don’t feel pretty.

812
00:54:36,820 --> 00:54:39,970
No matter how sad you are,
you never let anyone see you unkempt

813
00:54:40,470 --> 00:54:41,700
except me.

814
00:54:46,390 --> 00:54:47,800
Just say what you want to tell me.

815
00:54:56,120 --> 00:54:57,990
I’m sorry about the other day.

816
00:54:58,500 --> 00:55:00,700
I didn’t mean to say what I said.

817
00:55:02,160 --> 00:55:03,790
You always have a way to surprise me.

818
00:55:03,830 --> 00:55:05,600
I was just taken aback.

819
00:55:11,240 --> 00:55:13,300
Then what?

820
00:55:22,560 --> 00:55:24,600
I know that you mean well.

821
00:55:26,370 --> 00:55:29,500
You are the one
who knows everything about me.

822
00:55:33,160 --> 00:55:36,600
You are the only one I’m not afraid to cry
when watching a scene where a dog dies.

823
00:55:39,250 --> 00:55:41,300
You are the only one
who is in the memory space

824
00:55:41,540 --> 00:55:42,600
of my computer

825
00:55:43,620 --> 00:55:44,900
and my head.

826
00:55:47,500 --> 00:55:48,900
You are the only one…

827
00:55:52,700 --> 00:55:56,200
who I can share my stupid dream with
because you never look down on it.

828
00:56:03,740 --> 00:56:04,700
This place.

829
00:56:05,240 --> 00:56:08,000
It was where I asked you to be
my girlfriend when we were in college.

830
00:56:12,180 --> 00:56:13,800
It will also be the place…

831
00:56:17,060 --> 00:56:19,600
where I ask you to be my girlfriend again.

832
00:56:25,040 --> 00:56:26,700
I miss you so much.

833
00:56:30,420 --> 00:56:32,300
All the bad things in the past,

834
00:56:32,970 --> 00:56:34,500
it’s just the past.

835
00:56:36,610 --> 00:56:37,980
Let’s leave them behind.

836
00:56:40,850 --> 00:56:42,400
Let’s have a fresh start.

837
00:56:45,250 --> 00:56:49,200
I still want to share
my happiness with you.

838
00:57:02,980 --> 00:57:05,010
(Bambi still couldn’t get over her ex.)

839
00:57:05,310 --> 00:57:06,800
They had a big fight.

840
00:57:07,320 --> 00:57:08,500
It led to an accident.

841
00:57:09,230 --> 00:57:10,300
What accident?

842
00:57:11,120 --> 00:57:14,200
They were arguing
while they were in the car.

843
00:57:14,730 --> 00:57:15,970
They had an accident.

844
00:57:16,680 --> 00:57:17,970
Zee…

845
00:57:18,680 --> 00:57:19,690
She died.

846
00:57:20,080 --> 00:57:21,980
I think Bambi still can’t deal with it.

847
00:57:22,540 --> 00:57:25,300
That’s why she pretended
that she didn’t know me.

848
00:57:40,960 --> 00:57:42,100
I’m sorry.

849
00:57:44,800 --> 00:57:46,400
I want you to understand

850
00:57:46,810 --> 00:57:50,300
that I did everything

851
00:57:51,500 --> 00:57:53,370
because I want to see you happy.

852
00:57:54,490 --> 00:57:55,300
That’s all.

853
00:57:57,600 --> 00:57:58,900
I get it now.

854
00:58:03,450 --> 00:58:05,400
Don’t disappear from my life again.

855
00:58:07,950 --> 00:58:08,850
Can you do that?

856
00:58:15,950 --> 00:58:17,900
Don’t leave me, Bambi.

857
00:58:20,070 --> 00:58:21,100
I’m here now.

858
00:58:28,620 --> 00:58:29,600
Don't cry.

859
00:58:43,740 --> 00:58:45,770
If I knew getting back together
would be this good,

860
00:58:45,800 --> 00:58:47,300
I would have done it a long time ago.

861
00:58:47,870 --> 00:58:51,610
A straight girl like you enjoys playing
with the hearts of lesbians.

862
00:58:51,740 --> 00:58:54,130
You keep messing with me like this.

863
00:58:54,160 --> 00:58:55,290
Is it because you feel insecure
that Prim might be swayed?

864
00:58:55,320 --> 00:58:56,330
I’m not messing with you.

865
00:58:56,370 --> 00:58:57,130
I just want to be your friend.

866
00:58:57,270 --> 00:58:59,700
You called me your girlfriend.
Then you’ll be my girlfriend for tonight.

867
00:58:59,730 --> 00:59:01,600
It’s not easy to be my girlfriend.

868
00:59:01,700 --> 00:59:02,850
You are picky.

869
00:59:02,870 --> 00:59:04,510
You should go back
and enjoy the night with her.

870
00:59:04,560 --> 00:59:05,980
Are you jealous because of Kris?

871
00:59:06,010 --> 00:59:07,200
We had a great time back then.

872
00:59:07,230 --> 00:59:09,810
But I’m going to make today even better.
